                <summary>William Todd, son of James H. Todd, dislocated his neck after being thrown
                    from his horse on his way back from the fair. The efforts of Dr. S. Homer Henkel
                    could not save his life. He was taken to Mrs. Hamrick's after the accident.</summary>
