                <summary>Mrs. Lucretia Cox, wife of B. F. Cox, died in Staunton on September 15th of
                    consumption. She was 43 years old. "She was a member of the Presbyterian Church
                    for a number of years; lived the life of a christian, died in the triumphs of
                    faith, and has gone to her exceeding great reward. Her afflictions were great,
                    but she bore them with christian fortitude. She was in cheerful readiness and
                    waiting for death." She communicated words of hope to her brother, Rev. S. J.
                    Liggan, during her final hours.</summary>
                <note/>
